Offsite Consequence Analysis (OCA) Summary

The OCA for the system was reviewed and revised during preparation of this renewal. Scenarios were updated and the 2010 census data was used for the population estimates.

Facility Description and Site Layout

The Fresh Express facility located at 2370 W. Warrior Trail, Grand Prairie, Texas prepares and packages prepared salads.  Various types of fruits and vegetables (tomatoes, onions, grapes, apples, oranges, lettuce, cabbage, spinach, carrots and broccoli) are delivered to the facility, where they are washed, processed, dried, packaged and stored for shipment. 

A stationary anhydrous ammonia refrigeration system is used for room cooling and process water chilling.  The total anhydrous ammonia charge to the system is 15,000 pounds.  This ammonia refrigeration system is the only process at this site to which the RMP requirements are applicable.

